[Weekly Briefing] Road Atlanta - 2017s4 Week 4
[size=18][i][b]Welcome to the SRF![/b][/size]
We pride ourselves on a friendly, competitive and yet relaxed atmosphere both on and off-track. Don't be afraid to ask for help, either in practice sessions or on the forum![/i]

[img]http://members.iracing.com/jforum/posts/downloadAttach/2429685.page[/img]

[color=red][size=18]Spec Racer Ford Challenge Series @ [b] Road Atlanta Full[/b]
Week 4 of 12 - 2017 Season 4 [/size][/color]
Race Distance: [b]15 laps[/b], approximately 25 minutes
World Record lap time: [b]1:37.194[/b] by Jesse Sanchez
(n.b. random/dynamic weather impacts lap times greatly)

This week we visit the classic Road Atlanta circuit, using the full layout (after using the 'Short' layout earlier in the season). Road Atlanta is a challenging track with plenty of points to come unstuck but it also makes for fantastic racing. The draft is very strong, leading to race-long battles for position.

Target "planned" SoF race is usually 20:45 GMT Sunday, immediately following the Weekend Warriors league race.

[img]http://members.iracing.com/jforum/posts/downloadAttach/2429684.page[/img]

